attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Lucky!!! He might not have been so lucky in the past, but we hope he will be lucky in the future.  Lucky is almost 6 year old Labrador Retriever/Cattle dog mix who was surrendered to a kill shelter because the kids were no longer interested in him and the mother didn't want to pay for someone to watch the dog when they went on vacation!!! 

Lucky is amazingly affectionate, eager to please and housebroken. He bonds quickly with his owner and is protective of his both his home and owner. Because of this, he would make a great watchdog in a quiet household.  He should go to home with an experienced, adult dog owner and he must be the only dog in the house.  Lucky is very energetic and playful, he should get daily exercise, and a fenced in yard would be ideal.  

11th Hour Rescue now wants to give this sweet, loving boy the chance to find a family who will love him, appreciate him, and treat him like one of the family. Lucky has undergone training for leash manners and basic obedience.   

Lucky is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped.

Don't you want to be the one that shows Lucky that he can be part of a loving family?  If you're interested in Lucky go to EHRDOGS.ORG and submit an application.  Don't forget to ask for LUCKY HAVARD!!!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sacramento - Poppy is one of our long-term fosters. She has been in her foster home for 4 years. She came to us from Yolo County Animal Services Shelter after she was left behind in a trailer and her people moved without taking her. She is approximately 7 years old now and a lean 50 lbs. Poppy is a happy, active, athletic girl. She has spent a lot of time on training, and has spent a lot of time in pack walks (with an extremely responsible handler).  She loves to chase toys and do zoomies in the yard and leans into you for pets when she is done. Poppy prefers to be the only pet in the house though wouldn’t might not mind sharing her home with a lackadaisical, submissive male that will let her rule the house and not try to correct her (and with correct and proper intros) but mainly we think it is better for her to be a single pet. She is crate and house trained, spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccines. 

If interested, you can go online and find our adoption process and apply online at:     http://recycledpetsnorcal.org/adoptpet/

Adoption fee: $waived to the right family
attributes.name: Poppy

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello Gorgeous!

Daisy's DNA results are in, and she is such a unique mix! 

  • 25% Great Pyrenees
  • 12.5% Australian Shepherd
  • 12.5% Boxer
  • 50% MIX from groups that include Anatolian Shepherd, Central Asian Shepherd, Caucasian Shepherd, Rhodesian Ridgeback, Golden Retriever, Boerbel, and many others

Daisy has many of the characteristics of some of the breeds listed in the "MIX" section, including being independent and having a dominant personality. Although she looks a lot like a Pyrenees/Golden Retriever mix, she doesn't really have the temperament of either breed.

Daisy has very good manners in the house, but prefers a quiet home without too many visitors. She enjoys daily walks and generally does OK meeting most dogs on her walks.  Daisy is not always happy about meeting new people -- she isn't aggressive, but she doesn't trust easily. She has a scary bark and uses it to keep people from encroaching on her personal space.  She tends to accept people more easily if they have a dog, and the second time she sees them, she may basically ignore them. People who love dogs and think that most dogs love them back are often surprised that Daisy won't let them pet her.  She is definitely a one-family dog, and we think she would be happiest with a single owner or a couple, and no children.

Daisy currently lives in a foster home with several dogs, some her own size and some much smaller. She gets along with all of them, though will often find a quiet spot away from the others to take her nap. She previously lived in a foster home with a small dog and a senior cat, and everyone got along just fine.

If you live a nice quiet life and would give to Daisy the same love and devotion she will give to you, Daisy just may be the dog for you!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
We are busy caring for our foster animals, so if you have a question that's addressed in the bio, we are not able to respond.

Our adoption process is explained, in detail, so please don't email asking how you can meet the dog or cat.  Thank you!

Skye was born on March 11 2016.   She is very sweet and playful and  very curious. She wants to know everything you are doing. She loves to play in her cat tree. When you walk by her cat tree she will reach out and paw at you. She enjoys sitting in the  sun  in her hammock. She likes to sit on your shoulder and gives kisses. Sometimes she will sleep with you. She will meow to let you know that it is time for her can food. She is very vocal.  It is like living with a Siamese cat.  She doesn't mind if you carry her around. She is very good at using her scratching boxes. She always meows when you walk in the door. She has never been around small children. She would prefer adults and a home with no dogs. She likes everyone she meets.

Skye is spayed, micro chipped, up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines and tested negative for FIV/FELV.  Her adoption fee is $25.

Adoption Process:

Step 1: Complete a “no obligation” application on our website, www.pawprintsnky.com
Step 2: PawPrints will review the application, verifying Vet and personal references as well as landlord requirements/restrictions (if applicable)
Step 3: IF your application is approved, we will call you to schedule a meet and greet for you to meet the pet.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hotshot is a very special dog who needs a very special person.  Hotshot is very small child aggressive so should not be in a home with small children, and should be kenneled when they come to visit.  Hotshot is very protective of her person and may be a little fussy at others who come too near, even if they are adults, especially male.  At night he sleeps against the door in his foster mom's bedroom in order to protect her from any monsters that may try to sneak in and harm her.  He is like dynamite....small but explosive.

The ideal situation for this beautiful dog is a lady who lives alone and desires companionship.  Hotshot would gladly sit on their lap all day long.  He adores the person he bonds to and would very willingly give his life to protect her.

He does not do well with other dogs but usually just gets his bluff on them. 

Please apply online at www.louisianalifeline4k9s.org. As a purely foster based rescue, we do not have a central location where you can view our dogs and therefore we honor meeting request from pre-approved adopters. Completing the adoption application does not obligate you to anything, however, it gives us the chance to find your perfect match! Hotshot's adoption fee is $125, it includes all shots, neuter and microchipping.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Tigger, a high-energy bull terrier and pit bull mix born in late 2015,  is the friendliest, most fun-loving little guy. He absolutely loves everyone he meets. While he especially loves children he is better suited to older kids, not little ones.  He likes to be king of his castle, so he should be the only pet in his home. And his home should be in a quiet suburb with a fenced yard where Tigger can play and burn off his energy. He loves his people so much, he needs them to be home a lot.  If you are an experienced dog owner who can give Tigger the forever home he's looking for, fill out an application at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org  
 

RDR's adoption fees include the cost of spay/neuter/microchip at an RDR-approved facility, whether completed before adoption or if deferred because the pet is too young or has a medical issue.  All pets are also current on age-appropriate vaccines at the time of adoption

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Pepper was born about May 15, 2015 and weighs about 50 lbs.  She is a Joyful Rescues sanctuary pet because she arrived from the southern high kill shelter extremely fearful of humans, but she is wonderful with all the other dogs here.  Pepper never found a home because she has a very fast bite response to any human that moves too fast around her or in any situation where she feels uncertain what the human may do - even to reach out and pet her.  Every one here understands this and new humans in the house are told ahead of entering not to reach out to Pepper.  With this understanding of her behavior she has been living here and will continue to live here happily.  She enjoys the activity and the acreage playing with the other dogs and is welcome to stay as long as she lives.
 
Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility.
 
Can't Adopt Me?  SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link "Special Instructions to Seller" if you want to note a particular pet

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Nina was taken in by her foster family on the coldest night of the year in early 2016. Since then, she has decided that she loves the indoor cat life complete with the head scratches, toys, love, and of course food! Nina was born sometime in late 2014. 

Nina has become quite social and outgoing and loves playing with the other cats in her foster home. She is initially shy with humans, but has had no problem becoming friendly with her foster people (especially if they are making her food). Once she has warmed up to you, Nina is very vocal and quick to purr. Nina has had no problems with the dog in her foster home. She would do best with another cat in her furever home to play with.

Our kitties are vaccinated, spayed/neutered, negative for FIV and FeLV, wormed, and litter box trained.  Nina's adoption fee is $75. 

Please email felinefriendsnc@gmail.com for an application or fill out application online at http://www.felinefriendsnc.com/application.html

attributes.descriptionHtml: My name is Major Tom and, yes, I was named after the David Bowie song!  My foster mom thought I was a boy (hee, hee!!) but I fooled her!!  Still, she likes the name but calls me Tomi.   I am a beautiful, silky, petite tabby with a slightly longer over coat.  When I was a small kitten I had a very bad eye infection that left me with a watery eye but this does not detract from my beauty.  I don't let this stop me though.  I am very independent and do not like to be picked up a lot, but love to run around and play and sleep under the covers at night.  I am perfectly happy to be by myself and always find a way to keep myself occupied, or, I would love to play with a friend who has nice play manners.  Afterward I like to lay down by a human and sleep, especially on the couch (I love to lay on feet and legs!).  I have a very good appetite and eat all of the food in my bowl.  Foster mom always tells me how proud she is of my litter box skills.  My potential new family will need to make sure that I have plenty of scratching posts to scratch on as I really like to do that as well.  If you are interested in meeting me, please fill out an application online at northtexascatrescue.com and we can arrange a meeting!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Raider! Raider is a wonderful boy!  He is great with other animals and loves their company.  He also loves the company of adults but kids tend to make him a bit uncomfortable so he would probably do best in a home without kids.  He is also very handsome, but don't tell him yet, he doesn't know. :) Raider is non reactive to Cats, he's just a fun, overgrown Pup looking for a forever home.  He would do best in a home with another pet, no children and alpha parents.   Please consider giving Raider a home or foster home to call his own!

***************************************************************

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi. My name is Alex. I was born here. My brother  Bettis and I are the only ones left. You can already see that I'm quite handsome in my snazzy tuxedo! I'm a pretty cool cat around here. I love to talk..and well, sometimes talk back to you. I love attention, but I also like my alone time too. I crave  a home with someone to love me, but to also give me a place of my own for a little down time when I'm in the mood. I get along well with most cats, as long as they aren't too bossy, so a kitty friend would be nice.I have been neutered, vaccinated, combo tested (negative), and my preventives are up to date. If I sound like your kind of guy, fill out the adoption application on this website.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
After being on the run for 6 months Hannah is now ready for a home of her own. She has spent the last year in a foster home learning what it's like to be a loved member of a family. She must have a secure fenced in yard, another dog or dogs that she can bond with, and only older responsible children. Hannah loves dogs and all people once she warms up. She is super loving, goofy and playful. Hannah is still a flight risk though and can get nervous, so a family that is willing to work with her and give her time to settle will be a must, and she will love you forever! She is housebroken, spayed, microchipped, and up to date on shots. Any interested families will need a home check prior to adopting.
 

If Hannah might be the one for you go to EHRDOGS.ORG and submit an application.  Don't forget to ask for HANNAH STEELE!!!
attributes.name: Hannah Steele

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Look at this boy!  Fletcher is a sweet boy, with the right person/people.  He loves most of the volunteers at the shelter, but is very aloof with others, he seems to love women mostly.  He is perfectly content with hanging out on a shelf, but boy as soon as that door opens, he's right there for lovies.  He's a quiet boy and is selective of his kitty and people companions, but hey, maybe we all could take a lesson from him and be more selective of our companions ;)  If you think Fletcher is your guy, go ahead and fill out an adoption application!

Fletcher is up to date on vaccines, neutered, and micro chipped.   Please go to our website at www.emmetcountyanimalshelter.org to fill out the Cat Adoption Application.  All cat adoption fees are free will for approved applicants.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
DOB: June, 2015  

BREED/COLORING: Maltese/Poodle/Terrier Mix; Tan with White  (look thru all of his pix to see how long his hair grows... he can look very different from summer cut to winter coat!)

SIZE: Nerf weighs about 16lbs and is full grown. 

HISTORY:  Nerf was running loose in the desert for a couple of weeks. He finally came to a mechanic shop that took him in and contacted us to find him a home. 

PERSONALITY: Nerf is a total sweetheart and very people oriented. He wants laughs and loves and to Run! Run! Run! Lots of energy – but also lots of affection.

TRAINING: Nerf is at a cage-free kennel facility so we are not sure of his housebreaking skills. He may need some “rework” on his skills. 

WOULD DO BEST:  Nerf would love to have another dog – of any size – to play with and would like a yard space to run around and goof in. 

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Nerf does great with other dogs of all sizes. He is great with cats too. Nerf is not recommended for homes with young children because he can be a “door darter” and a runner. 

Vet Record: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).

Visit our website: http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/
attributes.name: Nerf

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello everyone!  My name is Sabor and guess what?  I am the world's sweetest dog!  Here are a few basic facts about me.  I am just a rescue dog and nothing fancy. I'm estimated to be around 10 years old. Looks like I am a chihuahua mix of some sort. I'm mostly black with some tan on my face and paws. I weigh about 14 pounds, and if you love me, you won't overfeed me because I sure love to eat. But I also love to take short walks and I'm great on a leash. The walks are good for me and you, and I don't pull on the leash at all. By the way, I am also great when I encounter other dogs or people.

In fact, I'm fabulous with other dogs. I live in a foster home with a bunch of other dogs and get along with everyone. I am a very laid back and low energy guy. I am crate trained and housetrained (if kept on a frequent schedule). I don't bark much either. I do have to tell you that I have several health issues and need to take medication twice a day. I take my pills very easily. Just put them in a bit of cheese or lunch meat or a pill pocket. I am very well controlled on my medication and, except for some hair loss and bigger-than-average tummy, you would never know that I have any health problems.

So you see, I'm just about perfect. I love to snuggle on your lap and I'm affectionate, but not needy. I would do great in a variety of homes. Toddlers and young children probably would not be my best match as I'm a mature fellow, but older ones are fine. I'm also adaptable and could easily enjoy life in an apartment or a house with a fenced yard. My only requirement is a loving home...Is that yours?

 
For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org  

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online.   http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms
attributes.name: Sabor

She is a beefy girl with a blocky head and the cutest stumpy legs. She enjoys cuddling, getting out for walks and field trips, and playing with her toys (especially ripping apart stuffed ones). She loves any tasty treat, but her favorite is a Kong toy stuffed with peanut butter. Gianna loves people, but is not a fan of other pets, so she'd like to find a family where she is their one & only "amore".

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Admiral is a neutered 6-year-old, super energetic Boxer/Mountain Cur mix. He is lean and athletic and loves running. He is the perfect companion for an active family.   He is house and crate trained and comes with a special escape-proof crate.  Admiral does need a fenced yard to run off his excess energy and needs a dog companion around his size..


He gets along with other dogs and loves playing wrestling and chasing/being chased. Admiral survived parvo as a little puppy and is now a handsome boy that wants nothing, but playing and being active.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I’m Yael. I was rescued from a Seal Beach alley with my three kittens a few years ago. What a relief it was to get off the street into a safe place. I was not used to being around people and I still don’t allow people to approach me but I don’t hide as much as I used to and no longer run for my life when someone enters my room at SBACC. I enjoy the company of other cats and am comfortable here. I wouldn’t mind living out my years where I’m loved and cared for by a wonderful team of volunteers and staff.  Maybe if the right person came along, I could adjust to a new home, but SBACC feels like home.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Our Diamond girl may look like a plain little black dog but she is anything but ordinary!  This little munchkin has a 100 watt  smile that can light up a room and brighten your day.  Despite having lost her home due to serious illness a while back, she is upbeat and entertaining and a joy to be around. 

Diamond loves to explore and it’s comical to watch her….whether she’s surveying the play yards, or investigating a pile of blankets on the floor.  She also loves car rides and walks with her best volunteer pals.  But right at the top of her list of favorite things, is getting loved on by her people!  If you talk to her and pet her, she will look into your eyes and hang onto your every word.  She’s such a special little girl.

Diamond has waited far too long for a home to replace the one she lost.  She has so much love to give and we want someone to love her in return.  She’s a nice tidy size, around 35 lbs. and she knows some basic commands.  She needs to be the only dog in the house, so if you’re looking for one special friend, she may be perfect for you!

Please give Diamond her second chance at finding a home and family.  You can fill out an adoption or foster application at www.ehrdogs.org and mention her name….DIAMOND BEAUFORT!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Rosey is a sweetheart with lots of love to give! She immediately flops over onto her belly when she sees people she loves and wants nothing more than to lounge around playing and cuddling them. She can be very timid and cautious around new people but with a bit of time she warms right up and becomes the happiest girl, you'll ever meet! She is a big goofball who loves toys and a big bed to curl up in and a person to snuggle up to. She would do well in a home with no other pets or small children. Rosey needs an experienced and patient owner who is ready to spend time to help her build her confidence and get past her fears.

Needs to work on slight stranger danger and socialization. Rosey has shown slight dog reactivity to some dogs while completely loving on whoever we place next to her kennel.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Strawberry was born about May 12, 2015 and is with us because her family is having a human baby.  So often the pets are considered disposable with this life changing event. The baby sure missed out on the opportunity of growing up with a sweet, wonderful kitty.  Maybe it's best overall, because Strawberry came to us in heat, and that will be her last one. Strawberry is just a social butterfly and will happily greet everyone she meet! She is great with other cats, dogs, and kids of all ages. She loves to go for car rides and also likes to help us fold laundry (see picture!) She is the sweetest cat you will ever meet. She comes when you call her and is happy to give you all the kitty kisses and head bonks you want. She has a wonderful purr that will relax you and she is really soft, so you will really love to hold her against you. And she LOVES to knead! She will adore you forever.  She is now spayed and ready to find a truly forever home.
 
Strawberry has recently developed FHV, feline herpes virus. It effects her right eye and is considered to be contagious to unvaccinated cats. She needs a special home where she can be the only cat, or be in a home that also has cats with this virus. Good nutrition is essential for her, in addition to L-lysine treats that are very effective in controlling flare-ups and also help to boost the immune system. 
 
Joyful Rescues remains committed to our Sanctuary Dogs and Cats. They will stay with us for their natural lives and we will care for and love them. We will be their forever family. We wish we could do it alone but we need your help. We are looking for people who can help us with Strawberries care. Please click the link below and donate. attributes.descriptionHtml:
None of our foster dogs are tested with cats because we have no way of testing them with cats. Siberians are notorious for their high prey drive and typically kill cats, rabbits, chickens, birds, squirrels, opossums, etc., so we don't have much success adopting them out to homes with cats. Most of our foster dogs are with us for killing cats, chickens and goats to begin with so our assumption is they are not good with cats and other small things that move. 

Siberians are typically good with children of all ages and the only reason we would not list them as not good with kids is because they may be too energetic and bouncy and knock over a toddler.

Southern Siberian Rescue is a volunteer based 501(c)3 organization based out of Raleigh, NC, so we do not have a physical facility with operating hours that you can visit to meet our dogs. All of our foster dogs are in our personal homes. You need to fill out our adoption application (http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption) and get approved to adopt and then we will set a time for you to meet our foster dogs. As a volunteer based group, we all have jobs, family, personal dogs and other commitments but we try to acknowledge and process applications as quickly as we can. That being said, we try to keep our available foster dogs as current as we can also but it is time consuming to get pics and information on new dogs so not all of our dogs are listed at all times. Please fill out our application and then we can discuss dogs that will work for you and your situation. We average 40-45 Siberians in our program so we are certain we have one that will work for you. Please know that we are not obligated to answer inquiries on dogs as we will focus on approved applicants. Again, there is ample time to discuss all of our foster dogs AFTER we have an approved application on file. We do adopt out of state as long as we can get a home check done. We ask that you, your family and existing pets make the trip to NC to meet and adopt our foster dogs. 

SSR can not and will not hold dogs for anyone. If we do, that means another Siberian will die in a shelter because a shelter dogs time is very limited, as is our foster space. We do our best to process applications in the order received and first application gets first interest in our foster dog(s). We understand that there will be scheduling conflicts with home checks and meet and greets but we will try to accommodate for that if a potential adopter has interest in a particular foster dog in our program.

All Southern Siberian Rescue foster dogs are microchipped, up to date on shots, spay/neutered, on monthly heartworm preventative and flea and tick preventative. For additional information on Southern Siberian Rescue and Siberian Huskies, please visit www.SouthernSiberian.com.

To fill out an application, please visit http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption .

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Personality: Nellie came to us completely matted and just a mess. The wooly coat requires much more grooming so she will need a home that understands that and gets her to the groomer. She is somewhat tolerant of brushing for short periods but if you try too long, she will snap at you. She is a happy, bouncy girl but can be the laziest sun bather and napper. She is cute as a button and will follow her people around but she does have a snappy side to her as well. She is startled by quick approaches and does not like to be led by her collar. You can leash her up just fine but she is untrusting if you try to lead her anywhere by her collar. She will put the brakes on and try to get away from you. Shortly after she came to us, she started having seizures. Her bloodwork is fine but her seizures lasted 4 plus minutes so she is now on phenobarb. She has not had another seizure since she has been on meds.

Energy Level: Low to Medium

Good with Dogs: Yes but only engages with a handful of dogs in her foster home.

Good with Children: Nellie can be a bit snappy sometimes so she will be best in a home with children 13 or older. She sometimes is freaked out by fast movements and might be anxious with young children and their exuberance.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Oink is a bulldog cross looking for a home. She is dog friendly, people friendly, and very sweet! Don't let that fool you though, she's a typical bulldog with a typical bulldog personality. If she doesn't want to do it, it isn't going to happen! 

Oink has pretty severe separation anxiety and needs to be on anti anxiety meds. She would do best with a stay at home person.

Oink has bad knees in both back legs, but the specialists have cleared her for a long healthy life with no surgery! She walks a little funny but that doesn't stop her! Oink will need someone willing to maintain her trim figure to not put further stress on her joints, and may need a joint supplement long term. But otherwise she is set to go!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
In 2014 Joyful Rescues returned from Tennessee with a little dog they called Fuzzy.  One look at her photo and we knew she was "the one".  Every day with this happy pup, now named Lily, reminds us of the tremendous gift Joyful Rescues gave us by saving her life.  So we dedicate this transport to Lily so that she, along with us, can "pay it forward" giving more beautiful animals a chance at a happy life.  Sincerely The Artful Gardener (727 Mt. Hope Ave., Rochester, NY)
 
Chloe was born about June 18, 2014 and weighs about 85 lbs. Chloe is a Joyful Rescues sanctuary dog as she was adopted out twice and returned leaving us to realize she wasn't going to make it in the real world and she is perfectly happy right here.  Chloe has made it very clear that she has found her forever home. Chloe is a one man girl and will not be sharing her heart with any other male, only her foster dad at JR.  Chloe is what some may call “un-adoptable .”
Joyful Rescues remains committed to our Sanctuary Dogs and Cats. They will stay with us for their natural lives and we will care for and love them. We will be their forever family.
We wish we could do it alone but we need your help. We are looking for people who can help us with Chloe’s care. Please click the link below and donate. Chloe thanks you.
https://www.paypal.com/donate
 
Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a "complete" pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY. 
 
Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility.

YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES
 
We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Calling #teamlabrador! We have a yellow lab boy named Rex who needs your help. 
 
This goofball truly is all lab and he’s an entertaining pleasure to spend time with. Rex’s first love is his bonded humans and he adores scritches and snuggles from his people. A *very* close second on his list of loves is the car. Rex could ride all day, gazing out the window, practicing his co-pilot skills, and appearing for all the world like he’s on the most important adventure mission ever. Like most dogs, #teamlabrador included, Rex is also a big fan of finding the important sniffs and eating the best snacks. 
 
Rex first found himself in need of rescue when he kept escaping the farm where he lived and a nearby vet’s office stepped in to get him help. Unfortunately, Rex’s current home is now shutting down and the property where he lives is being sold. 
 
Rex has some guarding behaviors as well as some fearful behavior that with a committed foster or adopter, we would love to have assessed through a qualified in home board and train before placing him. He will also come with post placement training support. Rex needs an adult only home but may have potential to live with both well matched dogs and cats depending on what the in home assessment tells us about his guarding behavior. Rex’s behavior is very manageable in a kennel setting but it’s been a long time since he’s lived in a home. In fact, we’re not sure he’s ever lived indoors so we’d like to set both Rex and his potential fosters/adopters up for safety and success. 
 
This boy has had no trouble capturing the hearts of his caregivers and they all want to ensure that his next steps are the very best ones possible for him. If you might be interested in meeting Rex, please contact us. You will love this sweet, silly boy!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
He's large and lovable, and the one thing he loves most in the world is to take a nap with a human! 

When someone sits in the big recliner and says, "Fraaaaaank ennnnnn" he comes a'runnin' and hops up by them, curls up, and is sound asleep in minutes. Nap time is valuable.

He enjoys playing, especially with dangly toys, and he loves attention.

Frankie walked up one day to his foster's house during a bad storm. We (the foster family) sheltered him in our garage, where we stored bags of dry cat food for the feral cats for a local feral cat organization. The next day, Frankie was sitting in the "man cave," fat and sassy. He'd torn open every bag of food and sampled each one! 

No owner could be found. Frankie was adult, unaltered, and free roaming, so he became an official foster.

But Frankie has an issue. Huge as he is, he's frightened of new people and new places. He's so beautiful, so lovable, so cuddly, our hope is someone will give him a chance when they come to meet him, and spend an hour or so waiting for him to feel comfortable. Could you be that person? 

Frankie gets along perfectly with other cats, and he even makes kitty friends easily. 

Contact his foster directly at: Mickey@mickeymarkets.com.

Frankie's adoption fee of $125 enables Happy Cat Adoptions to rescue more homeless kitties like Frankie.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
All of our dogs are housed in private homes, we do not have a store or a shelter.  We do not show dogs to interested parties until they have an approved adoption application.  If you are interested in adopting one of our dogs, please fill out an adoption application on our website www.helpingshepherdsofeverycolor.com  You may also find us on facebook:  Helping Shepherds of Every Color Rescue.

2/9/2020 Taz (was Zing) is being returned to the rescue due to some personal issues with his family.   Taz is very Energetic and loves to run.  He loves to go to the dog park and play with other dogs but for his home life it’s best if he’s an only dog. He’s a little food aggressive with other animals not with people at all. He’s not ok with little kids. He might be good with older kids, like around 8 and up though. He is also cautious when meeting new people but once he knows them he’s great. He loves sleeping on the sofa and getting belly rubs. He’s not big on toys but every once in awhile he’ll find one that he loves. He is also very nervous about getting his nails trimmed. Less is definitely more with him. I would not try to Restrain him, if you do then he’ll need a muzzle on. He does also have a little bit of anxiety and hates to be tied up. He does love his crate though, it’s like “his” place if that makes sense. 

6/29/2020:  Taz is NOT good with cats or other small animals. He is settling in to his new foster home.  He gets along with some dogs better than others. He needs time to warm up to new people but he is very loving when he is comfortable.

Tink's Story...

This beautiful little lady is Tink! Tink is 8 years old and the life of the party type dog and is always up for an activity! Tink loves to go for walks, car rides, and even knows how to run on the tread mill during inclement weather! She has excelled in all of her training and knows many commands like sit, down, place, come, and heel - her adopters will even receive free continued training to ensure her adoption is a success! That's how much we all love this girl  :)  She is fully housebroken and crate trained. Tink loves toys, giving kisses, and snuggling with her people at the end of the day!

Hi, my name is Rae.  My siblings and I were born in front of a Canadian compound in Kabul.  People would try to hurt us, so the kind humans brought us into the compound.  There were six of us in total.  The humans kept my other siblings but could not keep all of us so sent me and my sister, Raven to Nowzad to be looked after.  I am very friendly and get along well with other dogs.  I am also spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped.   I’m young and have lots of energy and will keep you entertained.

‘This companion animal is currently in the Nowzad shelter in Kabul, Afghanistan. If you are interested in adopting, then the Nowzad charity will supply you with video and photographs and should the adoption go ahead will fundraise and arrange the transport for this companion animal to come to your home’.

DOB: July 2011

BREED/COLORING:  Akita/Husky Mix; blue merle with white.

SIZE: Azulia is about 80lbs and is full grown.

HISTORY: Azulia was rescued of the streets in Tijuana by an independent rescuer who had seen her fending for herself. Polysfund.org stepped in and offered medical and transport to get her to safety.

PERSONALITY: Azulia is an absolute sweetheart. She loves having people around her but can be a bit weary of men (she may have been abused in Mexico). She's a character and a talker :)

TRAINING: Azulia has no training and could use some basic obedience training as she tends to jump on people. She is actually fairly good on leash (other than the jumping)... and she may need work on housebreaking as well.

WOULD DO BEST: Azulia would do well in a home with someone who is familiar with her breed mix. She absolutely requires a yard with 6 foot or higher fencing.

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Azulia could live with one other big, calm male dog with a proper introduction but is definitely not recommended for homes with female dogs, cats or tiny dogs. She was with children as young as 5 in her foster home in Mexico and did great with them.

VET RECORD: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).

Visit our website: http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/

Affectionate: Very

Cat Friendly: No

Child Appropriate: Older, 6+

My name is Bosco. 

They call me Mr. Wiggle Butt! Can you guess why? Because when I wag my tail, my entire back-half wiggles with excitement! Iwag rescued me from a high kill shelter and now I am ready to find my forever home! I have been with IWAG for a very long time, try 5 years too long! I love everyone here, but I'm ready to be in my fur-ever home. Could you be it? I'm even available through our HomeBuddies program, which means I can go home even quicker!

I am a lovable bundle of joy that loves to be pampered. Overall, I am an active dog but I can be calm and cuddle with you when it is time to rest. I would love to be the only dog in the family to give you all my attention. I love all people and children. I will be the perfect family dog!

Please come and visit me! I will love you unconditionally. I will wiggle my butt in excitement when I see you! I can’t wait!

Love, Bosco

attributes.descriptionHtml:
This beautiful boy is Sampson. He was adopted out as a puppy to a loving couple but recently has come back to Eleventh Hour. He is about 5 years old & he's an eager to please boy who loves to play with toys! His favorite thing to do is dig into our toy bucket and pick out toys to play with.

Sampson is very intelligent and has been through a board-and-train program! Sampson knows “sit” “down” “paw” “touch” “stay” “kisses” “OK”. Check out his video of him demonstrating his skills!! He absolutely loves butt rubs and can become very affectionate.

Sampson bonds strongly with his owners. He has a protective nature to him because he is so loyal, he would just need to be put away when guests come over and he doesn't mind it! He is the perfect balance of couch potato and hiking buddy. He could potentially live with another dog but it would likely have to be one with a more submissive personality.

If you are interested in Sampson, fill out an application and be sure to mention his name SAMPSON (SPERRY LONESTAR)!!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi … my name is Dillon! Read my bio to find out everything you need to know about me.  

If you think I might be the perfect pup for you, go to www.allamericanmuttrescue.org/forms and complete the adoption application online. If you are not able to adopt, please consider donating to AAMR in my name to help with my extended care in rescue.

Special needs pups are just that ... special ... and they just need special heroes to come to their rescue.  Have you tried on your hero cape lately?

We don’t know a lot about Dillon's early life other than a Good Samaritan took him in to keep him safe after he appeared to have been abandoned on a rural road.  His Good Sam said he sat in one spot on the road for several days and appeared to be waiting for his ‘ride’ to come back to get him.  After about 4 days, he gave up and went looking for food and water, which he found in her garage!

We do know that Dillon has some social anxiety issues and he can go from happy to distraught and nippy in situations with multiple people moving around in an area.  He has always done fine in his original foster home, but had a few 'incidents' in an adopting home, and he was returned to AAMR.  It is sad because Dillon is a very sweet and loving little guy ... until his anxiety takes over.  'Stranger Danger' is very real to him and in his mind, he needs to protect himself.

We are not really sure of Dillon’s breed mix.  He has a dachshund-like body (long and low) with the head of a tiny yellow lab!  Dillon really deserves a family who wants to help him develop some confidence and some manners so he can be the lucky dog he is meant to be.  He is very excitable and vocal when left alone for too long and will not be the best apartment resident. 

Dillon's wish list includes 1) a fenced yard, 2) an low-key, settled family willing to spend time with him and accept his limitations and 3) people to cuddle with every day who will teach him how to be the best boy ever.  Could that be you?

Dillon does well with most other dogs, so having another confident, friendly dog in the home may be good for him.  Absolutely no children in the home.  If there are children visiting the home, it will be best to give Dillon a safe, out-of-the-way area to rest in his crate while the children are around.  They make him very anxious.

Please read the rest of Dillon's bio below so you can learn more about him.

Approximate age/birthdate: ~ early 2015

Weight/size:  ~25 lbs

Housebroken:  YES ... as long as you do your part and let him outside often
 
Crate trained:  YES

Personality:  happy, playful, guarded in new situations, wary of new people and animals, anxious about too much activity around him

Energy level:  medium 
 
Fenced yard required?:   YES – he definitely needs a safe place to run off excess energy.  A physical fence is required so someone could not just wander in and trigger his anxiety.

Does he/she jump fences?  NO 

Leash walk:  YES
 
Obedience training:  Yes, a previous owner took him to class and we know he is very smart.

Riding in vehicles:  RIDES OK     

Spayed/neutered:   YES

Up-to-date on routine vaccinations:   YES

Microchipped:   YES

Social with other dogs:  Somewhat ... once properly introduced.  He gets excited when meeting new dogs and does not like dogs getting in his face.  He will growl if a new dog gets in his face.  Once he has time to properly meet a new dog, he generally does fine.   

Social with cats:  Do not know … has not been around cats. We think he would chase them if they ran, but not sure if he would try to harm them.

Good with children:  No Children ... he has nipped at children

Adoption donation:  $175 

We are an all-volunteer group, so please be patient and understand that it takes an average of 7-14 days to process the applications including reference checks, follow-up questions and home visits.  You can expedite the process by providing accurate email addresses for all your references.  Time to make phone calls is limited and we often have multiple applications in process.  We make every effort to move through them as quickly as possible. 

When your application is approved, we will schedule a meet-and-greet to see if Dillon picks you too.

If it seems that the adoption will be a good match for all, there is an adoption fee, and an adoption contract to be signed.

Please email AAMR at weluvpups@hotmail.com if you have additional questions.
attributes.name: Dillon

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hello, my name is Miss Kitty. I am a five year old pretty Tabby. I was brought to Rescue Ridge when my family moved and was not able to take me with them. I was living with them since I was a kitten and I'm very sad that we are not together anymore. Rescue Ridge is a nice place and the volunteers are kind and caring, but it's not the same as having a home to call your own. Please let me tell you about my charming personality. I am confident and  friendly with everyone I meet. I am curious and adventurous and I love to explore. I get along with other felines, but I need to be in charge. I am affectionate and I love spending time with my favorite people. I am up to date with my vaccines and I am spayed. If you would like to meet me, please send an email to  rescueridgeshelter@gmail.com . To apply to adopt me, please send an email to rescueridge.com.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Are you looking to adopt? If what you’re searching for is a personable, healthy, happy and playful dog... search no more! ShelleyMac is the perfect match for you!


ShelleyMac is intelligent, trusting, and loving 8-year old Labrador/Pittie mix, (8/26/12) who is SOOO full of life, love, excitement, and curiosity. You will quickly see that ShellyMac has an extremely sweet and happy disposition, and she has a constant smile on her face to prove it. Shelley would like to be an only child, no other pets, or children in the house as she wants you all to herself!


ShelleyMac has excellent house manners, is crate trained, but doesn’t really need to be crated. She answers to commands like come, sit, and stay, and barks only at appropriate times (such as when someone is at the door).


ShelleyMac LOVES playing fetch, riding in the car, getting hugged, kissed and cuddled!
 

It’s completely amazing that her big heart fits in her small body! If you decide to adopt ShelleyMac, you will consider yourself EXTREMELY lucky!! She’s definitely a keeper!!

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online.   http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org  

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Welcome to Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue, is an all volunteer animal welfare and rescue organization! Animals listed on our websites and other adoptable websites are available for adoption at our adoption house; Pounce & Fetch (512 Southview Blvd South St. Paul, MN 55075), we have no set hours, but we are always there cleaning and caring for the animals that reside at Pounce & Fetch! Please be aware of our sign on our front door. It will ask that you "Please knock, we are here cleaning" when you are more then welcome to come in and help us and visit the animals. Should it read "We are closed" means that we are not ready to receive guests and perhaps call to schedule at time or wait till the sign is flipped.

To start the journey of adopting a new family member from Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue you'll need to complete our adoption application. It is the first step toward possibly adding a new member to your family. You can either stop in at Pounce & Fetch to pick up and complete it or email us at adoptablepets@aol.com and we will send you the form, please complete and return via email.  Unanswered question could delay your application. Please don't be intimidated by our Adoption Application, its purpose in genuine. We have kept it simple for a reason so that we can get to know you and your family so that we can assist you with finding the right pet to join your family, forever! Please note that we are an all volunteer animal rescue and welfare organization, and there may be times where we may have to reschedule (several times too) the Meet & Greets, visiting at Pounce & Fetch as well as Home Visits. We so appreciate your understand and patience.

We are excited to assist you in your search and adoption of your new family member! Don't forget we are always seeking donations so that we can help the animals we rescue and save each and everyday! Please donate NOW so we can help them today! 651-888-2469 or 651-343-1964

attributes.descriptionHtml:
A Tail of the Good, the Not So Good, and the Ugly

The Good…

Lucas is a puppy mill survivor.  He is a handsome, white with liver spotting 6-8 year old IG.  Lucas is affectionate and wants nothing more than to be with you.  He loves to sit next to you on the sofa and makes a great lap warmer. He walks well on a leash and is crate trained.  He gets along with large and small dogs and is cat safe. 

The Not So Good…

Due to his years of living in a small, crowded cage, Lucas is afraid of big, open spaces, especially outdoors.  He usually has to be carried outside and will run back indoors if you leave the door open.  He will stay close to you while he is outdoors.  Potty training is a work in progress—he is about 80-85 percent reliable if kept on a schedule.  Lucas takes medication to help with his anxiety.

Lucas has come a long way since he was rescued from the puppy mill.  He still has the scars, but has made slow, but steady progress. 

The Ugly…

Lucas is one of the lucky ones who made it out of a puppy mill alive.  There are still hundreds of thousands dogs (and cats) who are trapped in a hell on earth.  Each of us can do something to help those still suffering in the mills.  Call a rescue group today and ask what you can do to help.

Lucas has a lot of love to give and will make a wonderful companion for someone who has a lot of love to give back and a lot of patience to help him continue on his journey to become a loving member of a loving home.  He is being fostered in San Antonio.

I was found, alone and so very pregnant and was about to pop! I had four beautiful kittens and they are ready to find permanent homes.

If you love to be hugged you should choose me! I am very affectionate and hug shoulders to show how appreciative I am to be safe. I am playful and kitten-like and enjoy tossing balls. My true passion is getting affection from humans. 

Like all good moms, I have been very protective of my kittens. My ideal home would be one where I can be with my daughter “Smalls” and be the only pets.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Ladies and Gentlemen, boys and girls, feast your eyes on the amazing Fernanda! Be stunned by her super-dog feats of “ball-manship!” Watch her leap tall bushes to save little children, so she can love them! 

Fernanda is a 4-year-old, 55-pound, female, pittie mix. Fernanda truly is an amazing dog. People call her the sweetest girl you will ever meet, but what does that mean? It means she loves everyone. She loves to run and play, so a fenced in yard would be the ideal outdoor environment for her.   Fernanda also loves children and loves to lay next to you because she just adores being with her people!  Fernanda's ideal indoor environment would be one where she is the "only furry child" and receives lots of love and attention from her family.

Fernanda “literally” will ask you to throw her ball until you are too tired to throw, and she will bring it back every time! Fernanda is house, crate, and leash trained, and she knows all her basic commands. She is also a world-class kisser with an infectious smile and a wiggle butt.

Remember how excited you were when the circus came to town. That's how Fernanda makes you feel everyday – it's hard to be down with Fernanda around. 

You can apply to adopt Fernanda at the web address below. At least come meet this girl and give her a chance to show you her fetch skills. 

 

 


An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online.   http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

Make a donation in this dog's name at http://www.angelsrescue.org/donate.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org  ​

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sweet Senior Edie is 11 years young – but still has plenty of pep in her step. She is very alert to everything around her and will follow you around the house to keep track of where her people are going. She will happily sit next to you with her paw on your arm while you pet and rub her.. She loves her toys and bones but does not like to share – we don’t blame her for that! She does allow her humans to take them away from her nicely. 

Edie lives with two other dogs and she does fine. They are not best friends but they like to co-exist with one another. The other dogs have learned to give Edie her space. She is crate and house trained (but prefers to not be in her crate). She knows her basic commands and loves puzzle toys! 

Edie does have DCM and gets medication twice a day. She also gets fish oil and CBD oil supplements for her joints to keep her young and moving! Edie would love a forever home to spend her golden years with! 

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
We are an all volunteer organization and we are overwhelmed with emails, so can only respond to those that ask questions not answered in the bio.  The adoption process is addressed in the bio.

Autumn

Available: Yes
Gender: Female
Age: 4 Yrs
Weight: 55 lbs
Breed: German Shorthaired Pointer/Pit Bull (best guess)
Spayed: Yes
Vaccinated: Yes
Microchipped: Yes
Adoption Fee: $200.00 (plus tax)

Foster Location: N Ky. Applicants must live within 2 hours of Florence, KY, no exceptions.

Home Recommendation: Single Family. Fenced yard. She tends to bark at sounds/people outside so a home that shares walls with neighbors would be stressful for all.

Kids: She loves everyone so the chances of her bowling over your kids are high.  Probably best to say no kids, or ones that can withstand a very strong dog barreling through them.

Crate Trained: Yes! All you have to do is say, "Crate!" and in she goes.

Potty Trained: Yes!


Dogs: She is okay with other dogs but will resource guard food and can redirect if overstimulated, so we think it would be safest for all if she's the only dog.

Cats: Nope!  She will chase them and can't be trusted.


Leash Manners: She's a puller.  Probably best to wear her out a bit before attempting a leash walk.

Autumn has been with us for a very long time.  She's a sweet girl who gets no attention from potential adopters.  

She loves life and does everything with great gusto (foster mom has received a couple of fat lips to prove it)  Autumn has energy for days, loves to spy on the neighbors (nothing gets past her).  She's a fun loving girl who will keep you entertained!



Her listing will be removed as soon as he has an approved application.
Most importantly, please be honest! We have many people tell us what they think we want to read, not what's truthful. If there are discrepancies, your application will be denied. It's important for us to place dogs in a home that's suitable. You may be a stellar owner but possibly not a good fit for the dog you were first interested in adopting. We're not trying to offend anyone, we're trying to set everyone up for success. We're a best fit rescue and will verify your vet and personal references.
Adoption Process:

Step 1: Complete a "no obligation" application on our website, www.pawprintsnky.com

Step 2: PawPrints will review the application, verifying Vet and personal references as well as landlord requirements/restrictions (if applicable)

Step 3: IF your application is approved, we will call you to schedule a meet and greet for you to meet the pet.

Step 4: If the meet and greet goes well, we will schedule the home visit.an meet the dog or cat.  Thank you!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Pretty Jarvie wandered up to a man while he was working in his yard. He thought she would leave and return home after awhile but she didn't. Jarvie was not wearing a collar with an ID tag and was not microchipped. FOUND DOG signs were posted around the neighborhood, in hopes of finding Jarvie's owners but sadly, no one responded. The man turned Jarvie over to Emmy's Hope Rescue in July 2016.

Jarvie is a very friendly, spunky girl. She likes the company of other large dogs and loves to run and play. She seems almost too interested in cats and probably should not be trusted with them. She's learning the basic commands: sit, down, stay. 

Estimated birth date: August 2014

Approximate weight: 65 lbs.

If you are interested in meeting Jarvie, please text or call Stephanie at: 281-622-6549.

*** CRITERIA for adopting from EHR***

YOU MUST:

1. Live in the Houston area (no more than an hour's drive away).

2. Be 21 years or older.

3. Have a fenced yard.  Fencing must touch the ground all the way around the yard.

4. We are looking for experienced pet owners. You must  have at least 2-3 years of good vet history, with your current and / or past dogs. Your vet record should show that you take your dog(s) to the vet annually for an exam and to update their Rabies and DHPP (distemper, parvo) vaccinations and heartworm testing, and that you purchase a monthly heartworm preventative.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi! My name is Cyrus. I am a special boy with a huge heart. My ideal home is a place where I am the only pet. My human needs to be a confident leader because I absolutely love having a routine. I have been through a lot of training and I am a champ on a leash. I also love going for car rides, playing ball, and lounging having some snuggle time. I need someone who understands what it means to have a dog that can't be with other dogs, and that needs to be left alone when I need my down time. I can be the biggest love bug you will ever meet, so despite my quirks I am a really great boy. Did I mention I am super handsome? Well, at least that's what all these people keep saying. They don't give me a mirror so I can only assume. If you think you might be the one I have been waiting for visit the rescue's website at www.fureverhomerescue.com and fill out an adoption application. You will not regret it! I promise to win you over in no time. 

Name:   Cyrus

Breed:   American Pitbull Terrier Mix

Adoption Fee:   $250

Date of Birth (estimated): 8/24 /2014

Weight:   66 lbs

Good with Dogs: no

Good with Cats: no

Good with Children: Older respectful children

House Trained:   yes

If you are interested in meeting or adopting this animal, please read the following before submitting an adoption application on our website - fureverhomerescue.com.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate vaccinations, 4Dx test (covers tick-borne diseases (A naplasmosis , Lymes, E hrlichiosis) as well as heart worm)    & de-worming.  We ask that our dogs live indoors unless otherwise stated & agreed upon.  We also ask that our applicants live in MN within a reasonable distance of the Twin Cities Metro area.

I need someone who understands what it means to have a dog that can't be with other dogs, and that needs to be left alone when I need my down time. I can be the biggest love bug you will ever meet, so despite my quirks I am a really great boy. Did I mention I am super handsome? Well, at least that's what all these people keep saying. They don't give me a mirror so I can only assume. If you think you might be the one I have been waiting for visit the rescue's website at www.fureverhomerescue.com and fill out an adoption application. You will not regret it! I promise to win you over in no time.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Age: 6 years old (approx)

Weight: 50 pounds

Adoption Fee: $175 (includes microchip, neuter surgery and vaccinations)

Papa is a very friendly medium-sized dog who is sweet and people-oriented. He knows how to SIT, lay down, and SHAKE hands and will even do this with either paw! He is quite playful but also a well-behaved adult dog. He likes car rides and going for puppacinos and frozen yogurt! He loves all people and loves to make new friends! We have also discovered he seems to enjoy wearing hats and sweaters, and he's so photogenic that you cannot help but dress him up for pictures! He's our resident Dog Model who will wear just about anything and has fun too. Got Netflix? He'll binge-watch whatever you're watching with you (we can't guarantee he'll stay awake though!) We have also found that Papa also really likes race tracks! He has been to Virginia International Raceway THREE times and loves all the people and noise. 

His ideal home would have no other dogs (cats who know dogs are OK) and no small children/toddlers (he jumps a little bit when he's excited and could knock a little child over without meaning harm). He likes to run around with balls so a fenced yard is required.

****************************************************************************

Papa is available for adoption through Spirit Canine Rescue. To adopt Papa, please visit our website http://www.spiritcaninerescue.org/adopt.html for more information and to complete an application. A home visit will be required prior to adoption. We request that all adopters be within reasonable traveling distance to Burlington NC.  

* Our only obligation is to the dogs in our program and we reserve the right to determine whether a particular dog and the adopter are the right fit. Remember, just because a dog "looks" like the one you want, that does not necessarily mean that the dog will "behave" like the one you want!

Note: We do not adopt out of state!  We do not adopt dogs into homes with invisible /underground fencing!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Thor is a gentle quiet boy who was found as a very hungry stray. He has FIV which means his immune system runs a little slow. He is a sweet boy who does not know that he is shut out of many adoption homes because people are afraid of the initials FIV

Feline Immunodeficiency Virus Infection (FIV) in Cats. The feline immunodeficiency virus (FIV) infection is a complex retrovirus that causes immunodeficiency disease in domestic cats. Immunodeficiency is the medical term used to describe the body's inability to develop a normal immune response.

Here are links to more information on FIV: http://www.vetstreet.com/our-pet-experts/why-this-vet-thinks-fiv-positive-cats-make-great-adoptees http://bestfriends.org/node/22322

Thank you for your interest in a Catsnap cat or kitten!

If you would like to meet a cat, please complete the online application
located on our website catsnap.org. 

We do not have a walk-in facility; most of our cats are in foster homes.
For this reason, we require an approved application on file before we set
up a meet and greet.

Completing an online application does not obligate you to adopt! We care
deeply about our cats and want the best match for all involved.
  • Vaccination against Panleukopenia (Distemper), Rhinotracheitis, and Calicivirus [cats] or DHLPP [dogs]
  • Vaccination against Rabies (if animal is over 4 months of age)
  • Testing for Feline Leukemia (FeLV) and Feline Immunodeficiency Virus (FIV) [cats] or Heartworm [dogs]
  • Initial de-worming, flea, and ear mite treatment
  • Sterilization of the animal prior to adoption; no exceptions
  • Micro-chipping as mandated by state law
  • One free veterinary exam within 10 days of adoption at participating clinics or coupon from a local Banfield.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Brandy was found completely emaciated showing every bone she had.  She was dirty and in some desperate need for some TLC. After a few weeks of food and care Brandy became very grateful.  She is one of the sweetest girls ever.  It might take some time when meeting new people to come around but when she does she's extremely loving.  While Brandy has associated with a few other dogs, she is typically very dog aggressive and should be kept as an only dog unless professional training corrects this trait. Brandy has lots of love to give and would make a great addition to any home without pets/small children.

As of 10/10/16 it's estimated Brandy is 5 years old.  Her heart worm status is yet to be known as she hasn't been vetted yet.  Brandy is house trained but may need a refresher course once in her new environment.  If interested in beautiful Brandy please submit an application to www.socorescue.com.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Lindsey was pregnant when she was picked up by animal control in a small East Texas town. She delivered 10 pups in the shelter, but one did not survive. It's really a testament to the care that shelter staff and volunteers provided that they lost only one, as a shelter is no place for newborn puppies. The shelter posted this precious family, looking for a rescue to take them. Great Pyrenees rescues across Texas turned them down because they are obviously mixes, and the rescues were already jam-packed with dogs and pups who looked more like Pyrs. Shelter staff had no choice but to add Lindsey and all her puppies to their list for euthanasia, which would have been a sad day for everyone. Thankfully, one of our foster moms volunteered to foster the whole family, and we were happy to take them into Bluebonnet Animal Rescue. We love our Great Pyrs, but we are not limited to just one breed, so it didn't matter to us that they are mixes.

We think Lindsey is a Great Pyrenees/Border Collie mix. She's friendly and playful, and loves people. Lindsey has been spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped.  She gets along well with other dogs, but can be a little bit alpha in her behavior.  She enjoys taking a dip in the wading pool to cool off in summer. Lindsey has a high prey drive and is NOT safe with livestock or cats.

If you have room in your heart and home for this beautiful girl, please read about our process and submit your application on our website: https://www.bluebonnetrescue.org/info/adoption.
attributes.descriptionText:
Lindsey was pregnant when she was picked up by animal control in a small East Texas town. She delivered 10 pups in the shelter, but one did not survive. It's really a testament to the care that shelter staff and volunteers provided that they lost only one, as a shelter is no place for newborn puppies. The shelter posted this precious family, looking for a rescue to take them. Great Pyrenees rescues across Texas turned them down because they are obviously mixes, and the rescues were already jam-packed with dogs and pups who looked more like Pyrs. Shelter staff had no choice but to add Lindsey and all her puppies to their list for euthanasia, which would have been a sad day for everyone. Thankfully, one of our foster moms volunteered to foster the whole family, and we were happy to take them into Bluebonnet Animal Rescue. We love our Great Pyrs, but we are not limited to just one breed, so it didn't matter to us that they are mixes.

We think Lindsey is a Great Pyrenees/Border Collie mix. She's friendly and playful, and loves people. Lindsey has been spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped.  She gets along well with other dogs, but can be a little bit alpha in her behavior.  She enjoys taking a dip in the wading pool to cool off in summer. Lindsey has a high prey drive and is NOT safe with livestock or cats.

If you have room in your heart and home for this beautiful girl, please read about our process and submit your application on our website: https://www.bluebonnetrescue.org/info/adoption.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Boris came to us from Kosovo about 4 1/2 years ago! He has been in a home this whole time, but unfortunately, he had to come back to Eleventh Hour Rescue as they were about to have a baby. Boris is a sweet boy, but he suffers from high anxiety and would not do well at all around a newborn baby. In fact, he would do best in an adults only home with minimal social traffic. He needs someone who is willing to work with him, and in return, he will love you to pieces.

Boris can not be left alone for long periods of time. He always wants to be with his person! He is frightened by other dogs, so would do best as an only pet. Boris would really benefit from daily exercise and mental stimulation games. He is just afraid of the world and has no other way to project it other than with anxiety... He needs a hero! 

If you are interested in being Boris' hero, visit EHRDOGS.ORG and fill out an application. Be sure to mention BORIS/JAX KOSOVO!!!!!!

Meet Diamond! 

Diamond is the girl with a 40-karat smile that lights up any room or yard she is in. She is a mega-watt cutie who hasn't let a single challenge dim that irresistible smile. Diamond would make a valuable companion for an active family that can (try to) keep up with her!

Miss Diamond has had a turbulent past; her former owner was unable to keep her and reached out to Adopt-A-Dog to try and re-home her. This resilient pup quickly settled in at our shelter, and started revealing the quirky personality underneath. Some of Diamond's favorite activities are: leaves, chin scratches and playing fetch. She is completely house-trained, and is now just looking for a family to take her on runs and who will always have a ball ready to play fetch.

This Diamond in the rough deserves a soft bed and pile of tennis balls to call her own. Fill out an application below if you are interested in bringing her home!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi, please let me introduce myself, my name is Sarah and I am a Lab/Jack Russell Terrier. I am house trained and crate trained, and love to go on walks and sniff around a securely fenced backyard.  Did I tell you that its me that pick all the tomatoes from the plants in the yard ? I am also spayed and have had all of my shots.

Sarah was abused by her first human family, so she finds it hard to trust new people and has fear aggression. It will take time to gain Sarah's trust and multiple meetings.  She needs an owner that can give her guidance (and plenty of treats) in situations when she feels insecure. After meeting a trainer Sarah have improved a lot and she responds to her special verbal command.  A training class would be a great adventure for Sarah and her new family. She will excel and perform as an A-student, she likes to learn and is eager to please. Building a relationship with Sarah will be time well spent, once she has overcome her insecurity and fear she is a GREAT active, loyal, and loving dog. 

Please come and meet me,  I need is a chance to find my permanent home. Older children only pleas e. 

 

Happy Days Dog and Cat Rescue microchips all dogs and cats before adoption. Microchips are implanted between the shoulder blades and are another form of identification should the animal get lost. The microchips are registered to  Happy Days Dog and Cat Rescue. The adopter's information is added once the adoption is complete. The adopter is responsible for a $19.99/Year registration fee or a $69.00/Lifetime registration fee to change information.  Dogs and Cats still need to have collar with tags should they get lost.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Chloe, our beautiful lab mix born in 2016, suffered a traumatic brain injury as a puppy. We've gone to great lengths for her and we hope you are willing to too!  Her sight and sense of smell are compromised and her hearing enhanced. Chloe is loving and fun, but preferably needs a home with retired or stay-at-homes, experienced with traumatic brain injuries or special education.  Chloe has mealtime frustration anxiety and prefers eating alone, knowing her morsels are hers alone.  A home where she can settle in before introductions to other pets would be great, but she may do best in a home without other dogs. Cats are okay!  A home with a fenced yard would be best. Chloe LOVES to run free like the wind. A home where a potty accident can be cleaned up and she can continue to learn that potty time outdoors reaps treats and indoors doesn't! We have faith she CAN do this, so should you!! A home where anti-seizure medications are lovingly administered and seizures patiently guided through. As much as she needs all this and more WE need this too because though none of us fit the criteria, we all love her.   She is up to date on her shots, microchipped and spayed.  If you would like to adopt Chloe, please put your application in here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
MACY is an almost 12 year old, medium sized, black and tan beauty, who was surrendered to a local shelter as part of a cruelty/neglect case along with her breeding partner. Macy was severely underweight, totally unsocialized, and unfamiliar with everything in her surroundings.

TEMPERAMENT

*** Macy is currently in boarding due to a lack of available foster homes!  Macy is looking for an experienced German Shepherd foster to stay with so we can get to know her better before finding her a great forever home.  
Please send an email to mogsfostermgr@gmail.com if you can help! ***

OTHER ANIMALS

Macy struggles to feel safe around other dogs, and has a strong small prey drive. She should be the ONLY pet in the home.

CHILDREN

Because of her history of severe abuse and neglect, Macy still has some unexpected reactivity, and would need to be in a home with no children. NO exceptions.

MEDICAL

Macy has been diagnosed with arthritis, and will require ongoing vet care for this condition.

This sweet girl does have some rough edges, and REQUIRES a strong, authoritative leader, who has experience in handling GSD's. Are you the one who can help this girl continue her journey of healing?

 

Macy's ADOPTION FEE:   $300
This fee covers only part of what we spend to vet, board and rehab the dogs we save. On average we spend over $450 on each dog. We made a decision to keep our adoption fee at the 2005 level even though vet prices have doubled and tripled since then. We are constantly fundraising to cover the deficit. At minimum, your adoption fee includes the dog's spay/neuter, heartworm test, heartworm treatment if needed, rabies shot, distemper/parvo shot, bordatella shot, deworming, monthly heartworm and flea preventives, and microchip. In many cases it also includes surgery and various types of vet treatment for standard issues such as hot spots, ear infections and so on.

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING Macy?
Complete an Adoption Application Now!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Mama Cecily and her 3 kittens (China, Conrad and Chip) were surviving outdoors at a construction site.  Every day Cecily and her babies were in danger due to the heavy equipment that was constantly moving in the parking lot where the kitty family would wait for someone to put some food out for them.  Luckily a Good Samaritan reached out to find help to bring this kitty family indoors to safety and warmth.

Cecily is only 1 year old herself...babies having babies.  She is a very sweet kitty and was a great Mama who protected her babies. Her Foster Mom says that she LOVES attention from her human and appears to be very glad to be finished with her "Baby Duties". She especially loves to sprawl out on the bed where she can sleep soundly without the constant fear of the outdoor dangers for her and her babies.  She promises to bring lots of love and happiness to her Forever Family.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, test for feline leukemia, de-worming, de-fleaing, etc.

To Adopt: www.CPAAdopt.org  or Text/Call Anita at 513-317-3343

Cecily is only 1 year old herself...babies having babies.  She is a very sweet kitty and was a great Mama who protected her babies. Her Foster Mom says that she LOVES attention from her human and appears to be very glad to be finished with her "Baby Duties". She especially loves to sprawl out on the bed where she can sleep soundly without the constant fear of the outdoor dangers for her and her babies.  She promises to bring lots of love and happiness to her Forever Family.



Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, test for feline leukemia, de-worming, de-fleaing, etc.



To Adopt: www.CPAAdopt.org  or Text/Call Anita at 513-317-3343

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Darla is a 12 - 13 year old, female, spayed, Boxer/Cattle Dog mix.  While Darla loves her human companions, she is picky about other four-legged companions.  She would do best as an only dog.

Darla is very eager to please her human. She loves the beach and swimming, going for walks and car rides. She knows her commands well (sit, stay, shake and lay down).  She will lay her head all the way onto the floor when you tell her "all the way down". She is a very quick learner. She loves to play fetch and playing with squeaky toys. She also loves getting packages in the mail, she will wait patiently for you to open the package and then beg for any bubble wrap. She will pop each bubble and then bring the plastic back to you.  She is kennel trained and will even go to her kennel when she thinks that you are about to leave.

If you have any questions, please contact us at hhfrescue@gmail.com.  If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application at www.hhfrescue.org.  Thank you for considering a rescued dog.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Petra is one of seven dogs who came into rescue together as working LGDs.  They spent their lives guarding goats on a  9600 acre ranch in the Texas Panhandle and were never properly socialized before coming to Bluebonnet. Petra was adopted then returned to us when she started climbing over the 4' fences at her new home. She returned to our pastures, which are enclosed with 5' fences, and everything was good, until she started going over OUR fences too.

We moved Petra to the house, where we have a yard with 6' tall fencing. She has assimilated into the routine of living inside the house, and even chooses to sleep in the crate most days, not because we put her there, but just because we keep the doors open on all our crates so the dogs learn to accept them as just another part of the furniture.

Petra is still very shy on meeting new people, but she does enjoy petting from her family. She is not one to bark unnecessarily, so she could be a great companion for someone who lives in town and has neighbors to consider.

Petra gets along with other dogs unless they bother her during meal times. Then, she doesn't hesitate to defend her bowl. She has never been one to play with other dogs, but recently, she has started making overtures to the male dogs in her foster home, trying to get them to play with her. Given her shy nature, we think it would be wonderful for Petra to have a confident dog in the home, so she can continue to follow that example, as she does in her foster home. She walks well on a leash, and is accustomed to walking with one or more big dogs.

If you think Petra would be the perfect addition to your family, please visit our website to read about our adoption process and submit your application.
